               <head>Majmu'ah</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89003718">
                  <summary>Collection or majmūʿah of works on religion, ethics, prayers, aphorisms, horology, astronomy, and calligraphy. Fine nastaʿlīq calligraphy and illumination. Not dated. Scribe: Darvīsh Muḥammad Qāsim Shīrāzī. Several ownership seals and inscriptions, some obliterated. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010108653" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item1">
                     <locus from="4" to="23r">ff. 4-23r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21881">Mukālimah-'i Mūsá bā Khudā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21881">مكالمهٔ موسى با خدا</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Story of the Prophet <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656093.0x000001 viaf_100646822" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n79058331" role="subject">Mūsá</persName>'s dialogue with Allāh on Mount Ṭūr
                        </p>
                        <p>Illuminated opening (ff. 4v-5r) of superlative quality, but with some damage</p>
                        <p>Prefixed (ff. 1r-2v) with a later introduction to the manuscript's contents of little value or information, dated 20 April 1846</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005357 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85045106" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item2">
                     <locus from="23v" to="29r">ff. 23v-29r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656495.0x000001 viaf_235145542615496640502">Iṣfahānī, Jamāl al-Dīn</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656495.0x000001 viaf_235145542615496640502">جمال الدّين اصفهانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21882">Tuḥfat al-vuzarāʾ va al-salāṭīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21882">تحفة الوزرأ و السّلاطين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Maxims and instructions on good governance, as part of the mirror of princes genre</p>
                        <p>The work is divided into 40 bāb grouped into 8 risālahs, followed by a conclusion or khātimah, which is lacking in this copy</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="3" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item3">
                     <locus from="29v" to="39r">ff. 29v-39r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <placeName/>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21883">Ilāhī'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21883">‏الهى ‌نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Sufi devotional work attributed to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_19703891" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n80013285" role="aut">ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad Anṣārī al-Hiravī</persName>, which is distinct from his <title>Munājāt</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Illuminated opening (ff. 29v-30r) of superlative quality, but with some damage</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112936" n="4" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item4">
                     <locus from="39v" to="44r">ff. 39v-44r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21884">ʿAlī maẓhar al-ʿajāʾib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21884">علی مظهر العجائب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Brief treatise by an anonymous author on the Shīʿah tradition explaining the revelation of the Arabic prayer, <title>Duʿāʾ Nādi ʿAlī</title>, by Archangel Jibrāʾīl to the Prophet <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_97245226" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n79130881" role="ant">Muḥammad</persName> in battle, enumerating 40 virtues for invocations to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50039100" role="subject">ʿAlī</persName>, deemed the 'manifestation of marvels' 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="5" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item5">
                     <locus from="44r" to="52v">ff. 44r-52v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7067">ʿAlī ibn Maḥmūd al-Ḥājj</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7067">على ابن محمود الحاجّ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21885">Nuzhat al-ʿāshiqīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21885">نزهت العاشقين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Brief manual of ṣūfī teachings</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007101189 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85045106" n="6" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item6">
                     <locus from="53r" to="56v">ff. 53r-56v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_11350">Kunūz al-rumūz</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_11350">کنوز الرموز</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymously compiled collection of the aphorisms of sages, completed before the 1530s</p>
                        <p>The work is organised into 10 parts, each mentioning 10 points of merit, concluding with a khātimah, lacking in this copy</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85045106" n="7" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item7">
                     <locus from="56v" to="59r">ff. 56v-59r</locus>
                     <author/>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21886">Tuḥfat al-suʿadāʾ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21886">تحفة السّعدأ</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Religious and ethical council in 40 points</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111617 " n="8" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item8">
                     <locus from="59r" to="65r">ff. 59r-65r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21887">al-Risālat al-mansūbah fī al-asʾilat va al-ajvibah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21887">الرّسالة المنسوبة فى الاسئلة و الاجوبة</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Record of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50039100" role="ant">ʿAlī</persName>'s replies to 40 questions raised by the King of Rūm, addressed to the Companions of the Prophet
                        </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007101548 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2001000141" n="9" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item9">
                     <locus from="65v" to="67v">ff. 65v-67v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymous treatise possibly entitled <title>Risālah fī aḥkām al-kavākib al-sabʿah</title>, describing the negative and positive influences of the seven stars
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009116093 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85062073" n="10" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item10">
                     <locus from="68r" to="69r">ff. 68r-69r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21888">Risālah dar maʿrifat-i awqāt-i sāʿāt-i ayyām-i asābīʿ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21888">رساله در معرفت اوقات ساعات ايّام اسابيع</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Essay on hours assigned to each planet over the course of seven days, attributed to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_17355947" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr90029093" role="att">Abū Maʿshar Balkhī</persName>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2001000141 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007101548" n="11" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item11">
                     <locus from="69r" to="72r">ff. 69r-72r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21332">Ikhtiyārāt-i qamar dar burūj-i is̲nā ʿashar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21332">اختيارات قمر در بروج اثنا عشر</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Tractate in masnavi form on auspicious positions of the moon in relation to the 12 signs of the zodiac, usually attributed to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_12392936" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n82136884" role="att">Nāṣir al-Dīn Ṭūsī</persName>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005940" n="12" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item12">
                     <locus from="72r" to="74r">ff. 72r-74r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on the interpretation of dreams, with phenomena organised in alphabetical order and omens associated with the same alphabetical letter</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89002521" n="13" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3786-item13">
                     <locus from="74r" to="87r">ff. 74r-87r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Versified manual on the art and impliments of calligraphy, dated <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">920</date>/<date calendar="Gregorian">1514</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>Scribe: Darvīsh Muḥammad Qāsim Shīrāzī</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658639.0x000001 viaf_70819144">Mashhadī, Sulṭān ʿAlī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658639.0x000001 viaf_70819144">مشهدى، سلطان على</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21889">Risālat ādāb al-khaṭṭ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21889">رسالة آداب الخطّ</title>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
